The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Mortaza out of tri-series
                                                                                                                       7                                      Mortaza out of tri-series
                      
	Dhaka: Bangladesh skipper Mashrafe Mortaza has been ruled out of next months tri-series against India and Sri Lanka at home after failing a fitness test, the Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) said .         
	Mortaza underwent surgery on both knees in Australia in September and was looking to return for the series.         
	Medically he looks fit but he did not get his full cricketing fitness yet, chief selector Rafiqul Alam said.All-rounder Shakib al-Hasan will lead in Mortazas absence. Pacer Shafiqul Islam is the only uncapped player.         
	The Squad         
	Shakib al-Hasan (captain), Mushfiqur Rahim, Mohammed Ashraful, Abdur Razzak, Tamim Iqbal, Syed Rasel, Roqibul Hassan, Mahmud Ullah, Nazmul Hossain, Naeem Islam, Imrul Kayes, Rubel Hossain, Shahriar Nafees, Aftab Ahmed, Shafiul Islam. (Reuters)                                                                                                                     
